<div class='toload theorem'>
<p><span class='envidentifier'>Theorem 1.3.11
<span style='font-weight: normal;'>[<span class='ref' data-tag='MR2304314'></span>, Theorem 5.18]</span></span>
Let $\mathcal{G}$ be a topological groupoid and let $m:\mathcal{G}^{(2)}\to G$, $m(a,b)=ab$ be the product map. The following are equivalent:
<ol class='arpar'>
	<li> $\mathcal{G}$ is Ã©tale.</li>
	<li> $\mathcal{G}^{(0)}$ is open and $m$ is a local homeomorphism.</li>
	<li> $\mathcal{G}^{(0)}$ is open in $\mathcal{G}$ and $m$ is an open map (or equivalently, the product of open sets in $\mathcal{G}$ is open).</li>
	<li> $\mathcal{G}^{(0)}$ is open and the source map $\mathfrak{s}:\mathcal{G}\to\mathcal{G}^{(0)}$ is an open map.</li>
</ol>
</p>
</div>